         <div>
            <head>6.8.1885 Donnerstag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49289">Rigi Kaltbad</placeName> August 6. 1885. Thursday.</p>
            <p>Worked at the Känzli in the morning and began my direction West to the Scheideck by
               rail in the afternoon. Got caught in a fearful shower so that we did not see much.
                  <persName key="1863">Valentin</persName> told his unavoidable Bonaparte
                  story and proposed himself as the Chirany Chatanoj in Noahs ark when the
               carriage was darkened. When we came home found traité from <orgName key="67188">Lemerre</orgName> and his accounts. He gives <persName key="103">Mamma</persName>
               2195 francs but says he is going to give her more. He pays her 40 centimes a volume
               for the first 2000, 50 c. for numbers 2000 to 10000 and 60 c. for all over 10000.
               Read <name type="work" key="28748">Madame de Mineleko</name> in the evening.. Cholera
               came to <placeName key="48967">Marseilles</placeName>. Over 40.000 people have died
               and 10000 been attacked in Spain already. Much worse than last year when only 20,000
               died in Spain (500), France and Italy together. Political horizon rather black.
               England and Russia again rather quarrelsome. France and Germany not on best terms. I
               am reading the <name type="work" key="28729">Société de Londres</name> by a
               &#x201e;Diplomate Etranger&#x201c;<note type="reg">
                  <persName key="4200">Vasili</persName>
               </note> well written and interesting.</p>
         </div>
